summary: Completed comprehensive testing of CineVault movie/TV tracker app. Backend APIs fully functional, frontend working with minor fixes applied.

ui_bugs.issue: TypeError: title.toLowerCase is not a function when title is JSX element
SelectItem components cannot have empty string values

design_issues.issue: Missing Description or aria-describedby for accessibility

passed_tests: Backend API health check - all endpoints responding correctly
User CRUD operations - create, read, delete users working
Watchlist CRUD operations - create, read, update, delete watchlists
Watchlist item management - add/remove items from watchlists
TMDB API endpoints - returning empty data as expected (no API keys configured)
User selection page - loads correctly with 'Who's watching?' interface
User creation flow - create new profile with name and avatar color
Home page navigation - displays trending/popular sections (empty due to no TMDB API)
Navigation bar functionality - Home, Movies, TV Shows, My Lists links working
Watchlist creation - successfully creates new watchlists
Page routing - proper navigation between different sections

success_percentage.frontend: 90% - Core functionality working, minor UI fixes applied

action_item_for_main_agent: Consider adding TMDB and OMDB API keys to enable movie/TV data fetching. Add aria-describedby attributes to Dialog components for better accessibility. The app is fully functional for user management and watchlist operations.
